\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4789066 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14181748\charrsid12455492 Ah, ah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11555284 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14181748\charrsid12455492 Did your mother ever have a chance to get out and attend any women's functions or ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4789066 LC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14181748\charrsid12455492 No, she was always too busy. Mother, poor mother, was always at home. I mean, firstly, if there was any,
 any of us, er, well, if we didn't see her in the room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2441644\charrsid12455492 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14181748\charrsid12455492 
 "Where are you, Mum" everyone used to always say that, me always said that, ye-, ye-.
